  "contamination_note": "The raw kernel run reported n_donors_expected=11633 and 11372 missing_donors. This was a real bug: donor_id is a pandas Categorical whose dtype carries the full census-wide category list (same root cause as the pseudobulk run), so obs_df[\"donor_id\"].value_counts() returned ~11372 spurious zero-count donor entries from other census datasets. All spurious entries were assigned zero cells and piled into whichever batch had the lowest real cell load (batch 1, which logged an inflated \"11404 donors\" during the run). The fields above have been filtered to the real 261 dev-cohort donors. Independently verified against results/l2_dev_donor_metadata.csv (already committed, previously verified): 261/261 donors match exactly, 0 cell-count mismatches, sum of per-donor cell counts == 1,263,676 both ways. The actual embedding computation was unaffected by this bug -- verified separately by exact per-batch real cell-count matches against an independent local dry-run of the same batching logic."
